    teach_p:"We don't teach from books. We teach from decades of living, healing, building and beginning again. Every skill we share is one we practice daily.",
    tc1_who:"Tobias",tc1_name:"Medicine & Longevity",
    tc1_desc:"I started as a nurse in Swiss hospitals. Over the years that shifted — less fixing symptoms, more understanding why people get sick in the first place. Today my work sits at the edge of clinical medicine and ancestral health: how do you actually stay well for a long time?",
    tc2_who:"Julia",tc2_name:"Classical Tantra",
    tc2_desc:"I studied Sanskrit in Nepal and India. Not because it was on trend — because I needed to read the original texts myself. What I found has nothing to do with what people call Tantra today. It's a complete map of consciousness. That's what I teach.",
    tc3_who:"Julia",tc3_name:"Qigong & Yoga",
    tc3_desc:"Years of daily practice. Not as exercise — as a way of relating to the body. Qigong works with energy directly. Classical yoga is a technology for waking up. Together they change the way you inhabit yourself. That's the only way I know how to teach them.",
    tc4_who:"Tobias & Julia",tc4_name:"Plant Medicine & Ceremony",
    tc4_desc:"We've both been sitting in ceremony for over a decade — with indigenous teachers, in different countries, through things we can't fully put into words. What we offer is held, safe, and real. We don't call it an experience. We call it medicine.",
    tc5_who:"Tobias & Julia",tc5_name:"Sacred Systems",
    tc5_desc:"Human Design, Gene Keys, Numerology, Palmistry. Four systems, one purpose: understanding who you actually are. We give personal readings — not theory, not apps, just direct insight grounded in how we use these maps ourselves every day.",
    tc6_who:"Tobias",tc6_name:"Permaculture & Off-Grid Living",
    tc6_desc:"Magic Land exists. We built it. The food forest, the water systems, the community structure — all of it started with a piece of land and a lot of trial and error. If you want to build something like this yourself, come learn from someone who's actually done it.",
    roots_label:"Roots",roots_h2_1:"Ancient lines.",roots_h2_em:"Living now.",
    roots_q:"We didn't choose these lineages. They chose us.",
    roots_body:"Tobias carries the name Jeronimo — after the Apache warrior who refused to surrender his way of life. That refusal lives in everything he builds. Julia grew up carrying the old knowledge of Crimean Russia — Tatar, Slavic and Eastern healing traditions that survived centuries of silence. We don't treat these as heritage. We treat them as responsibility.",
    land_label:"Koh Phangan · Thailand",land_h2_1:"Magic",land_h2_em:"Land",
    land_desc:"Our sanctuary. A large piece of land surrounded by untouched nature — no neighbours, pure jungle, complete privacy. We're developing it sustainably for living, ceremony, and food production. A place to build, grow, heal and gather. Everything we teach, we practice here first. Visitors by invitation.",
    land_tag:"Koh Phangan · Thailand",
    pill1_title:"Permaculture",pill1_text:"Food forest, aquaculture and water systems — growing food the way nature intended.",
